1
00:00:07,041 --> 00:00:09,208
Katara, voice-over:
WATER.

2
00:00:09,250 --> 00:00:10,875
EARTH.

3
00:00:10,917 --> 00:00:13,208
FIRE.

4
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:16,125
AIR.

5
00:00:16,166 --> 00:00:19,917
LONG AGO, THE FOUR NATIONS
LIVED TOGETHER IN HARMONY.

6
00:00:19,959 --> 00:00:24,333
THEN EVERYTHING CHANGED WHEN
THE FIRE NATION ATTACKED.

7
00:00:24,375 --> 00:00:27,625
ONLY THE AVATAR,
MASTER OF ALL FOUR ELEMENTS,

8
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:28,583
COULD STOP THEM.

9
00:00:28,625 --> 00:00:30,333
BUT WHEN THE WORLD
NEEDED HIM MOST,

10
00:00:30,375 --> 00:00:32,083
HE VANISHED.

11
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:33,917
A HUNDRED YEARS PASSED,
AND MY BROTHER AND I

12
00:00:33,959 --> 00:00:37,500
DISCOVERED THE NEW AVATAR,
AN AIRBENDER NAMED AANG.

13
00:00:37,542 --> 00:00:39,583
AND ALTHOUGH HIS AIRBENDING
SKILLS ARE GREAT,

14
00:00:39,625 --> 00:00:43,041
HE HAS A LOT TO LEARN BEFORE
HE'S READY TO SAVE ANYONE.

15
00:00:43,083 --> 00:00:46,291
BUT I BELIEVE AANG
CAN SAVE THE WORLD.

16
00:00:55,875 --> 00:00:59,083
- IT'S BEEN SO LONG
SINCE I'VE HAD HOPE,

17
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:02,500
BUT YOU BROUGHT IT BACK TO
LIFE, MY LITTLE WATERBENDER.

18
00:01:02,542 --> 00:01:04,458
AANG IS THE AVATAR.

19
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:07,000
YOU BOTH FOUND HIM
FOR A REASON.

20
00:01:07,041 --> 00:01:11,000
NOW YOUR DESTINIES
ARE INTERTWINED WITH HIS.

21
00:01:11,041 --> 00:01:14,250
ACCORDING TO LEGEND,
YOU NEED TO FIRST
MASTER WATER,

22
00:01:14,291 --> 00:01:16,000
THEN EARTH, THEN
FIRE, RIGHT?

23
00:01:16,041 --> 00:01:17,583
THAT'S WHAT
THE MONKS TOLD ME.

24
00:01:17,625 --> 00:01:19,792
WELL, IF WE GO
TO THE NORTH POLE,

25
00:01:19,834 --> 00:01:21,500
YOU CAN MASTER
WATERBENDING.

26
00:01:21,542 --> 00:01:23,834
WE COULD LEARN IT TOGETHER!

27
00:01:23,875 --> 00:01:27,000
THERE HAVE BEEN
MULTIPLE SIGHTINGS
OF THE AVATAR,

28
00:01:27,041 --> 00:01:29,750
BUT HE IS IMPOSSIBLE
TO TRACK DOWN.

29
00:01:29,792 --> 00:01:31,792
THIS COWARD'S HUNDRED
YEARS IN HIDING ARE OVER.

30
00:01:38,625 --> 00:01:39,625
[BIRDS SINGING]

31
00:01:48,834 --> 00:01:49,834
[MOMO CHATTERING]

32
00:01:51,917 --> 00:01:54,750
- GREAT. YOU'RE BACK.
WHAT'S FOR DINNER?

33
00:01:54,792 --> 00:01:56,667
WE'VE GOT
A FEW OPTIONS.

34
00:01:56,709 --> 00:02:00,333
FIRST, ROUND NUTS AND SOME KIND
OF OVAL-SHAPED NUTS.

35
00:02:00,375 --> 00:02:03,250
AND SOME ROCK-SHAPED NUTS
THAT MIGHT JUST BE ROCKS.

36
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:07,333
DIG IN.

37
00:02:07,375 --> 00:02:10,834
SERIOUSLY,
WHAT ELSE YOU GOT?

38
00:02:10,875 --> 00:02:11,500
[PURRING]

39
00:02:17,041 --> 00:02:18,250
[BOOM]

40
00:02:18,291 --> 00:02:20,000
Sokka: WHAT WAS THAT?

41
00:02:23,208 --> 00:02:25,083
[BOOM]

42
00:02:25,125 --> 00:02:27,500
Aang: IT'S COMING
FROM OVER THERE.

43
00:02:27,542 --> 00:02:32,083
Sokka:
SHOULDN'T WE RUN AWAY FROM
HUGE BOOMS, NOT TOWARD THEM?

44
00:02:34,208 --> 00:02:35,667
[PURRING]

45
00:02:41,041 --> 00:02:42,458
HYAH.

46
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:43,834
AN EARTHBENDER.

47
00:02:43,875 --> 00:02:45,250
LET'S GO MEET HIM.

48
00:02:45,291 --> 00:02:48,125
HE LOOKS DANGEROUS,
SO WE BETTER APPROACH
CAUTIOUSLY.

49
00:02:48,166 --> 00:02:50,125
HELLO THERE!
I'M KATARA.

50
00:02:50,166 --> 00:02:51,750
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

51
00:02:51,792 --> 00:02:53,166
AH!

52
00:02:59,208 --> 00:03:02,166
Aang: NICE TO MEET YOU!

53
00:03:02,208 --> 00:03:04,041
I JUST WANTED TO SAY HI.

54
00:03:04,083 --> 00:03:06,250
HEY, THAT GUY'S
GOT TO BE RUNNING
SOMEWHERE.

55
00:03:06,291 --> 00:03:07,834
MAYBE WE'RE
NEAR A VILLAGE.

56
00:03:07,875 --> 00:03:10,333
AND I BET THAT VILLAGE
HAS A MARKET.

57
00:03:10,375 --> 00:03:12,458
WHICH MEANS
NO NUTS FOR DINNER.

58
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,750
HEY! I WORKED HARD
TO GET THOSE NUTS.

59
00:03:14,792 --> 00:03:16,041
[PURRING]

60
00:03:16,083 --> 00:03:17,125
YEAH, I HATE THEM, TOO.

61
00:03:25,250 --> 00:03:27,291
Aang: GREAT HAT.

62
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,041
I'LL TRADE YOU
SOME NUTS FOR IT.

63
00:03:32,166 --> 00:03:34,709
HEY!

64
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:36,250
HI, MOM.

65
00:03:36,291 --> 00:03:37,291
WHERE HAVE
YOU BEEN, HARU?

66
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:38,875
YOU'RE LATE!

67
00:03:38,917 --> 00:03:40,250
GET STARTED
ON YOUR CHORES.

68
00:03:40,291 --> 00:03:42,041
HEY! YOU'RE THAT KID.

69
00:03:42,083 --> 00:03:43,625
AH!

70
00:03:43,667 --> 00:03:45,625
WHY DID YOU
RUN AWAY BEFORE?

71
00:03:45,667 --> 00:03:47,417
UH...YOU MUST
HAVE ME CONFUSED
WITH SOME OTHER KID.

72
00:03:47,458 --> 00:03:49,667
NO, SHE DOESN'T.
WE SAW YOU EARTHBENDING.

73
00:03:52,083 --> 00:03:53,875
THEY SAW YOU
DOING WHAT?

74
00:03:53,917 --> 00:03:55,375
THEY'RE CRAZY,
MOM.

75
00:03:55,417 --> 00:03:56,500
I MEAN,
LOOK AT HOW
THEY'RE DRESSED.

76
00:03:59,125 --> 00:04:01,291
YOU KNOW
HOW DANGEROUS THAT IS.

77
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:04,542
YOU KNOW WHAT WOULD HAPPEN
IF THEY CAUGHT YOU EARTHBENDING.

78
00:04:04,583 --> 00:04:05,959
Man: OPEN UP!

79
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:06,625
[LOUD KNOCKING]

80
00:04:08,208 --> 00:04:10,208
Sokka:
FIRE NATION. ACT NATURAL.

81
00:04:20,166 --> 00:04:22,125
AAH!

82
00:04:22,166 --> 00:04:24,875
WHAT DO YOU WANT?
I'VE ALREADY
PAID YOU THIS WEEK.

83
00:04:24,917 --> 00:04:26,959
THE TAX JUST DOUBLED.

84
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,041
WE WOULDN'T WANT
AN ACCIDENT, WOULD WE?

85
00:04:29,083 --> 00:04:32,959
FIRE IS SOMETIMES
SO HARD TO CONTROL.

86
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:42,959
YOU CAN KEEP
THE COPPER ONES.

87
00:04:47,625 --> 00:04:49,333
NICE GUY.

88
00:04:49,375 --> 00:04:51,166
HOW LONG HAS
THE FIRE NATION
BEEN HERE?

89
00:04:51,208 --> 00:04:54,333
FIVE YEARS.
FIRE LORD OZAI

90
00:04:54,375 --> 00:04:57,125
USES OUR TOWN'S
COAL MINES
TO FUEL HIS SHIPS.

91
00:04:57,166 --> 00:04:59,583
THEY'RE THUGS.
THEY STEAL FROM US.

92
00:04:59,625 --> 00:05:01,417
AND EVERYONE HERE
IS TOO MUCH OF A COWARD

93
00:05:01,458 --> 00:05:02,959
TO DO ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

94
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,125
QUIET, HARU!

95
00:05:04,166 --> 00:05:05,750
DON'T TALK
LIKE THAT!

96
00:05:05,792 --> 00:05:06,917
BUT HARU'S
AN EARTHBENDER.

97
00:05:06,959 --> 00:05:08,208
HE CAN HELP.

98
00:05:08,250 --> 00:05:10,166
EARTHBENDING
IS FORBIDDEN.

99
00:05:10,208 --> 00:05:12,750
IT'S CAUSED
NOTHING BUT MISERY
FOR THIS VILLAGE.

100
00:05:12,792 --> 00:05:14,959
HE MUST NEVER USE
HIS ABILITIES.

101
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,834
HOW CAN YOU SAY THAT?

102
00:05:16,875 --> 00:05:18,500
HARU HAS A GIFT.

103
00:05:18,542 --> 00:05:20,000
ASKING HIM NOT TO EARTHBEND

104
00:05:20,041 --> 00:05:22,500
IS LIKE ASKING ME
NOT TO WATERBEND.

105
00:05:22,542 --> 00:05:24,000
IT'S A PART OF
WHO WE ARE.

106
00:05:24,041 --> 00:05:25,792
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

107
00:05:25,834 --> 00:05:28,583
I UNDERSTAND THAT HARU
CAN HELP YOU FIGHT BACK.

108
00:05:28,625 --> 00:05:30,417
WHAT CAN THE FIRE NATION
DO TO YOU

109
00:05:30,458 --> 00:05:31,875
THAT THEY
HAVEN'T DONE ALREADY?

110
00:05:31,917 --> 00:05:34,417
THEY COULD TAKE HARU AWAY,

111
00:05:34,458 --> 00:05:36,166
LIKE THEY TOOK HIS FATHER.

112
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:46,458
Haru: MY MOM SAID
YOU CAN SLEEP HERE TONIGHT.

113
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,542
BUT YOU SHOULD LEAVE
IN THE MORNING.

114
00:05:48,583 --> 00:05:50,792
THANKS. I'LL MAKE
SURE APPA DOESN'T
EAT ALL YOUR HAY.

115
00:05:56,959 --> 00:05:59,458
Katara: I'M SORRY ABOUT
WHAT I SAID EARLIER.

116
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:00,667
I DIDN'T KNOW ABOUT
YOUR FATHER.

117
00:06:00,709 --> 00:06:02,792
Haru: THAT'S OK.

118
00:06:02,834 --> 00:06:05,750
IT'S FUNNY. THE WAY
YOU WERE TALKING
BACK IN THE STORE,

119
00:06:05,792 --> 00:06:07,834
IT REMINDED ME
OF HIM.

120
00:06:07,875 --> 00:06:09,000
THANKS.

121
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:11,041
MY FATHER WAS VERY COURAGEOUS.

122
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:13,000
WHEN THE FIRE NATION INVADED,

123
00:06:13,041 --> 00:06:15,375
HE AND THE OTHER EARTHBENDERS
WERE OUTNUMBERED 10 TO 1.

124
00:06:15,417 --> 00:06:16,959
BUT THEY FOUGHT
BACK ANYWAY.

125
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,959
HE SOUNDS LIKE A GREAT MAN.

126
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:22,333
AFTER THE ATTACK,
THEY ROUNDED UP MY FATHER

127
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:24,166
AND EVERY OTHER EARTHBENDER

128
00:06:24,208 --> 00:06:27,291
AND TOOK THEM AWAY.
WE HAVEN'T SEEN THEM SINCE.

129
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:29,542
SO THAT'S WHY YOU HIDE
YOUR EARTHBENDING.

130
00:06:29,583 --> 00:06:30,750
YEAH.

131
00:06:30,792 --> 00:06:33,083
THE PROBLEM IS,

132
00:06:33,125 --> 00:06:36,000
THE ONLY WAY I CAN FEEL
CLOSE TO MY FATHER NOW

133
00:06:36,041 --> 00:06:39,166
IS WHEN I PRACTICE
MY BENDING.

134
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:41,208
HE TAUGHT ME
EVERYTHING I KNOW.

135
00:06:43,542 --> 00:06:45,083
SEE THIS NECKLACE?

136
00:06:45,125 --> 00:06:46,667
MY MOTHER GAVE IT TO ME.

137
00:06:46,709 --> 00:06:48,208
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

138
00:06:48,250 --> 00:06:50,250
I LOST MY MOTHER
IN A FIRE NATION RAID.

139
00:06:50,291 --> 00:06:52,959
THIS NECKLACE IS
ALL I HAVE LEFT OF HER.

140
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,458
IT'S NOT ENOUGH,
IS IT?

141
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:55,667
NO.

142
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:02,959
- AAH! HELP!

143
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:03,959
THE MINE!

144
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,750
AAH...

145
00:07:06,792 --> 00:07:10,000
HELP ME!

146
00:07:10,041 --> 00:07:11,750
[MOANING]

147
00:07:11,792 --> 00:07:14,166
[RUMBLING]

148
00:07:14,208 --> 00:07:16,542
AH! IT'S NOT WORKING.

149
00:07:16,583 --> 00:07:18,291
WE HAVE TO GET HELP.

150
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:20,625
THERE'S NO TIME.
PULL HARDER!

151
00:07:20,667 --> 00:07:22,875
HARU, THERE'S A WAY
YOU CAN HELP HIM.

152
00:07:22,917 --> 00:07:24,667
I CAN'T.

153
00:07:24,709 --> 00:07:26,834
PLEASE. THERE'S
NO ONE AROUND TO SEE YOU.

154
00:07:26,875 --> 00:07:27,792
IT'S THE ONLY WAY!

155
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:38,375
AH!

156
00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:42,041
HARU, YOU DID IT!

157
00:07:48,834 --> 00:07:50,959
[PURRING]

158
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,667
IT WAS SO BRAVE OF HARU
TO USE HIS EARTHBENDING

159
00:07:53,709 --> 00:07:55,125
TO HELP THAT OLD MAN.

160
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:57,208
YOU MUST HAVE
REALLY INSPIRED HIM.

161
00:07:57,250 --> 00:07:58,875
I GUESS SO.

162
00:07:58,917 --> 00:08:00,083
EVERYONE SHOULD
GET SOME SLEEP.

163
00:08:00,125 --> 00:08:01,792
WE'RE LEAVING
AT DAWN.

164
00:08:01,834 --> 00:08:03,000
DAWN? CAN'T WE
SLEEP IN FOR ONCE?

165
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:04,750
ABSOLUTELY NOT!

166
00:08:04,792 --> 00:08:06,875
THIS VILLAGE IS CRAWLING
WITH FIRE NATION TROOPS.

167
00:08:06,917 --> 00:08:08,834
IF THEY DISCOVER
YOU'RE HERE, AANG,

168
00:08:08,875 --> 00:08:10,041
WE'LL BE EATING
FIREBALLS FOR BREAKFAST.

169
00:08:10,083 --> 00:08:11,750
GOOD NIGHT.

170
00:08:11,792 --> 00:08:13,583
I'D RATHER EAT
FIREBALLS THAN NUTS.

171
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:15,000
GOOD NIGHT.

172
00:08:15,041 --> 00:08:16,750
[LAUGHING]

173
00:08:37,041 --> 00:08:38,083
AH!

174
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:39,750
THAT'S HIM!

175
00:08:39,792 --> 00:08:41,750
THAT'S THE EARTHBENDER!

176
00:08:41,792 --> 00:08:42,959
AAH!

177
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:12,542
THEY TOOK HIM!

178
00:09:12,583 --> 00:09:14,834
THEY TOOK HARU AWAY!
WHAT?

179
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:16,709
THE OLD MAN TURNED HIM
IN TO THE FIRE NATION.

180
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:19,208
IT'S ALL MY FAULT.
I FORCED HIM INTO EARTHBENDING.

181
00:09:19,250 --> 00:09:22,000
SLOW DOWN, KATARA.
WHEN DID THIS HAPPEN?

182
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:24,333
HARU'S MOTHER SAID
THEY CAME FOR HIM
AT MIDNIGHT.

183
00:09:24,375 --> 00:09:26,625
THEN IT'S TOO LATE
TO TRACK HIM.
HE'S LONG GONE.

184
00:09:26,667 --> 00:09:27,959
WE DON'T NEED
TO TRACK HIM.

185
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,417
THE FIRE NATION
IS GOING TO

186
00:09:29,458 --> 00:09:30,750
TAKE ME RIGHT
TO HARU.

187
00:09:30,792 --> 00:09:33,208
AND WHY WOULD
THEY DO THAT?

188
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:35,834
BECAUSE THEY'RE GOING TO
ARREST ME FOR EARTHBENDING.

189
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,208
I THOUGHT YOU WERE CRAZY
AT FIRST, KATARA,

190
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:43,041
BUT THIS MIGHT WORK.

191
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:44,750
THERE ARE VENTILATION
SHAFTS THROUGHOUT THESE MINES.

192
00:09:44,792 --> 00:09:46,792
ALL AANG HAS TO DO IS
SEND AN AIR CURRENT

193
00:09:46,834 --> 00:09:48,500
FROM THAT VENT
TO THIS ONE RIGHT HERE.

194
00:09:48,542 --> 00:09:50,583
THE BOULDER LEVITATES
AND TA-DA--

195
00:09:50,625 --> 00:09:52,041
FAKE EARTHBENDING.

196
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:54,041
AANG, DID YOU GET
ALL THAT?

197
00:09:54,083 --> 00:09:55,875
SURE, SURE.
I GOT IT.

198
00:09:55,917 --> 00:09:57,583
DO YOU REMEMBER YOUR CUE?

199
00:09:57,625 --> 00:09:59,375
YEAH, YEAH.
JUST RELAX.

200
00:09:59,417 --> 00:10:01,500
YOU'RE TAKING ALL
THE FUN OUT OF THIS.

201
00:10:01,542 --> 00:10:04,041
BY "THIS" DO YOU MEAN
INTENTIONALLY BEING CAPTURED

202
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:05,959
BY AN ARMY OF
RUTHLESS FIREBENDERS?

203
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,625
EXACTLY.
THAT'S FUN STUFF.

204
00:10:08,667 --> 00:10:10,667
Sokka: HERE THEY COME.
GET IN YOUR PLACES.

205
00:10:12,667 --> 00:10:15,458
UH! GET OUT OF MY WAY,
PIPSQUEAK.

206
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:18,125
HOW DARE YOU
CALL ME PIPSQUEAK,

207
00:10:18,166 --> 00:10:20,709
YOU GIANT-EARED
CRETIN?

208
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:22,417
WHAT DID YOU
CALL ME?

209
00:10:22,458 --> 00:10:24,500
A GIANT-EARED
CRETIN.

210
00:10:24,542 --> 00:10:26,083
LOOK AT
THOSE THINGS.

211
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:28,291
DO HERDS OF ANIMALS
USE THEM FOR SHADE?

212
00:10:28,333 --> 00:10:30,500
YOU BETTER BACK OFF!

213
00:10:30,542 --> 00:10:31,709
SERIOUSLY,
BACK OFF.

214
00:10:31,750 --> 00:10:33,792
I WILL NOT BACK OFF!

215
00:10:33,834 --> 00:10:35,542
I BET ELEPHANTS
GET TOGETHER

216
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:38,333
AND MAKE FUN
OF HOW LARGE
YOUR EARS ARE.

217
00:10:38,375 --> 00:10:40,709
THAT'S IT!
YOU'RE GOING DOWN.

218
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:42,959
I'LL SHOW YOU
WHO'S BOSS,

219
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,041
EARTHBENDING STYLE.

220
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:51,834
I SAID,
"EARTHBENDING STYLE!"

221
00:10:55,959 --> 00:10:58,667
THAT LEMUR.
HE'S EARTHBENDING.

222
00:11:00,834 --> 00:11:02,959
NO, YOU IDIOT.
IT'S THE GIRL.

223
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,542
OH. OF COURSE.

224
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:08,250
I'LL HOLD HER!

225
00:11:08,291 --> 00:11:10,375
[WHISPERING]
YOU'VE GOT 12 HOURS
TO FIND HARU.

226
00:11:10,417 --> 00:11:11,667
WE'LL BE
RIGHT BEHIND YOU.

227
00:11:19,417 --> 00:11:22,667
MOMO, YOU HAVE
SOME BIG EARS.

228
00:11:22,709 --> 00:11:23,583
[PURRING]

229
00:12:00,834 --> 00:12:04,417
SHE'LL BE FINE, AANG.
KATARA KNOWS WHAT SHE'S DOING.

230
00:12:12,083 --> 00:12:15,834
Man: EARTHBENDERS,
IT IS MY PLEASURE TO WELCOME YOU

231
00:12:15,875 --> 00:12:18,291
ABOARD MY MODEST SHIPYARD.

232
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:20,917
I AM YOUR WARDEN.

233
00:12:20,959 --> 00:12:23,917
I PREFER TO THINK OF YOU
NOT AS PRISONERS,

234
00:12:23,959 --> 00:12:26,834
BUT AS HONORED GUESTS.

235
00:12:26,875 --> 00:12:28,959
AND I HOPE YOU
COME TO THINK OF ME

236
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:33,208
AS YOUR HUMBLE
AND CARING HOST.

237
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:35,875
YOU WILL SUCCEED HERE
IF YOU SIMPLY ABIDE--

238
00:12:35,917 --> 00:12:37,542
[COUGHING]

239
00:12:41,417 --> 00:12:45,625
WHAT KIND OF GUEST DISHONORS
HIS HOST BY INTERRUPTING HIM?

240
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:47,375
TAKE HIM BELOW.

241
00:12:47,417 --> 00:12:51,417
ONE WEEK IN SOLITARY
WILL IMPROVE HIS MANNERS.

242
00:12:51,458 --> 00:12:54,750
SIMPLY TREAT ME WITH
THE COURTESY I GIVE YOU

243
00:12:54,792 --> 00:12:58,750
AND WE'LL GET ALONG
FAMOUSLY.

244
00:12:58,792 --> 00:13:00,959
YOU WILL NOTICE,
EARTHBENDERS,

245
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:04,709
THAT THIS RIG IS MADE
ENTIRELY OF METAL.

246
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:08,792
YOU ARE MILES AWAY
FROM ANY ROCK OR EARTH.

247
00:13:08,834 --> 00:13:11,792
SO, IF YOU HAVE ANY ILLUSIONS
ABOUT EMPLOYING

248
00:13:11,834 --> 00:13:14,875
THAT BRUTISH SAVAGERY
THAT PASSES FOR BENDING

249
00:13:14,917 --> 00:13:18,375
AMONG YOU PEOPLE,
FORGET THEM.

250
00:13:18,417 --> 00:13:21,166
IT IS IMPOSSIBLE.

251
00:13:21,208 --> 00:13:23,083
GOOD DAY.

252
00:13:48,667 --> 00:13:49,959
KATARA?

253
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,500
HARU!

254
00:13:51,542 --> 00:13:52,917
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

255
00:13:52,959 --> 00:13:54,709
IT'S MY FAULT
YOU WERE CAPTURED.

256
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,792
I CAME TO RESCUE YOU.

257
00:13:56,834 --> 00:13:58,834
SO YOU GOT
YOURSELF ARRESTED?

258
00:13:58,875 --> 00:14:00,750
IT WAS THE ONLY WAY
TO FIND YOU.

259
00:14:00,792 --> 00:14:03,041
YOU'VE GOT GUTS, KATARA.
I'LL GIVE YOU THAT.

260
00:14:03,083 --> 00:14:06,834
COME ON. THERE'S SOMEONE
I WANT YOU TO MEET.

261
00:14:06,875 --> 00:14:11,208
KATARA, THIS IS
MY FATHER, TYRO.

262
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:13,792
DAD, THIS IS KATARA.

263
00:14:13,834 --> 00:14:15,166
IT'S AN HONOR
TO MEET YOU.

264
00:14:15,208 --> 00:14:18,750
HAVE SOME DINNER, KATARA.

265
00:14:18,792 --> 00:14:21,041
EW.

266
00:14:21,083 --> 00:14:22,875
IT'S NOT AS BAD
AS IT LOOKS.

267
00:14:24,875 --> 00:14:26,500
EEW!

268
00:14:26,542 --> 00:14:28,375
IT'S STILL
PRETTY BAD, THOUGH.

269
00:14:28,417 --> 00:14:30,709
TYRO, THE PRISONERS
ARE COMPLAINING

270
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:32,333
THERE AREN'T ENOUGH
BLANKETS TO GO AROUND.

271
00:14:32,375 --> 00:14:34,250
I'LL TALK TO THE GUARDS.

272
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:36,792
IN THE MEANTIME, MAKE SURE
THE ELDERLY ARE TAKEN CARE OF.

273
00:14:36,834 --> 00:14:39,917
THE REST OF US WILL SIMPLY
HAVE TO HOPE FOR WARMER WEATHER.

274
00:14:39,959 --> 00:14:41,709
IF YOU DON'T MIND
ME ASKING,

275
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:42,709
WHAT'S YOUR
ESCAPE PLAN?

276
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:44,625
EXCUSE ME?

277
00:14:44,667 --> 00:14:46,458
YOU KNOW, THE PLAN
TO GET EVERYONE
OFF THE RIG?

278
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,458
WHAT IS IT?
MUTINY, SABOTAGE?

279
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:51,291
THE PLAN?
THE PLAN IS TO SURVIVE,

280
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:54,166
WAIT OUT THIS WAR,
HOPE THAT ONE DAY

281
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:56,917
SOME OF US CAN GET BACK HOME
AND FORGET THIS EVER HAPPENED.

282
00:14:56,959 --> 00:14:58,709
HOW CAN YOU SAY THAT?

283
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:00,709
YOU SOUND LIKE YOU'VE
ALREADY GIVEN UP.

284
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:03,291
KATARA, I ADMIRE
YOUR COURAGE.

285
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:05,333
AND I ENVY YOUR YOUTH.

286
00:15:05,375 --> 00:15:07,959
BUT PEOPLE'S LIVES
ARE AT STAKE HERE.

287
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,709
THE WARDEN IS
A RUTHLESS MAN,

288
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:13,125
AND HE WON'T STAND
FOR ANY REBELLION.

289
00:15:13,166 --> 00:15:16,291
I'M SORRY,
BUT WE'RE POWERLESS.

290
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:17,375
WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT.

291
00:15:20,875 --> 00:15:23,542
EARTHBENDERS!

292
00:15:23,583 --> 00:15:26,625
YOU DON'T KNOW ME,
BUT I KNOW OF YOU.

293
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:30,083
EVERY CHILD IN MY WATER TRIBE
VILLAGE WAS ROCKED TO SLEEP

294
00:15:30,125 --> 00:15:32,208
WITH STORIES OF THE BRAVE
EARTH KINGDOM

295
00:15:32,250 --> 00:15:35,417
AND THE COURAGEOUS EARTHBENDERS
WHO GUARD ITS BORDERS.

296
00:15:35,458 --> 00:15:37,625
SOME OF YOU MAY THINK
THAT THE FIRE NATION

297
00:15:37,667 --> 00:15:39,792
HAS MADE YOU POWERLESS.

298
00:15:39,834 --> 00:15:42,709
YES. THEY HAVE TAKEN AWAY
YOUR ABILITY TO BEND.

299
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:45,000
BUT THEY CAN'T TAKE AWAY
YOUR COURAGE.

300
00:15:45,041 --> 00:15:47,667
AND IT IS YOUR COURAGE
THEY SHOULD TRULY FEAR,

301
00:15:47,709 --> 00:15:49,792
BECAUSE IT RUNS DEEPER
THAN ANY MINE

302
00:15:49,834 --> 00:15:51,792
YOU'VE BEEN FORCED TO DIG,

303
00:15:51,834 --> 00:15:54,250
ANY OCEAN THAT KEEPS YOU
FAR FROM HOME.

304
00:15:54,291 --> 00:15:56,083
IT IS THE STRENGTH
OF YOUR HEARTS

305
00:15:56,125 --> 00:15:58,250
THAT MAKE YOU WHO YOU ARE,

306
00:15:58,291 --> 00:16:01,166
HEARTS THAT WILL REMAIN UNBROKEN
WHEN ALL ROCK AND STONE

307
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:02,583
HAS ERODED AWAY.

308
00:16:02,625 --> 00:16:04,917
THE TIME TO FIGHT BACK IS NOW!

309
00:16:04,959 --> 00:16:08,625
I CAN TELL YOU
THE AVATAR HAS RETURNED!

310
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:10,709
SO REMEMBER YOUR COURAGE,
EARTHBENDERS!

311
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:14,333
LET US FIGHT FOR OUR FREEDOM!

312
00:16:14,375 --> 00:16:16,625
[MAN COUGHING]

313
00:16:46,792 --> 00:16:48,125
AH!

314
00:16:48,166 --> 00:16:48,917
SHH.

315
00:16:53,417 --> 00:16:55,083
YOUR 12 HOURS ARE UP.
WHERE IS HARU?

316
00:16:55,125 --> 00:16:56,458
WE'VE GOT TO
GET OUT OF HERE.

317
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:58,667
I CAN'T.

318
00:16:58,709 --> 00:17:01,166
WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME.
THERE ARE GUARDS EVERYWHERE.

319
00:17:01,208 --> 00:17:02,291
GET ON!

320
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:04,041
KATARA, WHAT'S WRONG?

321
00:17:04,083 --> 00:17:06,125
I'M NOT LEAVING.

322
00:17:06,166 --> 00:17:09,000
I'M NOT GIVING UP
ON THESE PEOPLE.

323
00:17:13,792 --> 00:17:16,250
Sokka: WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
YOU'RE NOT LEAVING?

324
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:18,125
WE CAN'T ABANDON
THESE PEOPLE.

325
00:17:18,166 --> 00:17:20,166
THERE HAS TO BE
A WAY TO HELP THEM.

326
00:17:20,208 --> 00:17:23,000
MAYBE SHE'S RIGHT.
WHAT DO YOU SAY, SOKKA?

327
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:24,041
I SAY YOU'RE
BOTH CRAZY.

328
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:28,959
LAST CHANCE.
WE NEED TO LEAVE NOW.

329
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,583
NO.

330
00:17:30,625 --> 00:17:32,959
I HATE WHEN YOU
GET LIKE THIS.

331
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,083
COME ON, WE BETTER HIDE.

332
00:17:36,166 --> 00:17:37,125
[WHISPERING]
GO.

333
00:17:41,458 --> 00:17:43,333
LOOK!

334
00:17:43,375 --> 00:17:46,959
TELL ME EXACTLY
WHAT YOU SAW.

335
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,834
WELL, SIR, IT LOOKED
LIKE A FLYING BISON.

336
00:17:48,875 --> 00:17:50,417
WHAT?

337
00:17:50,458 --> 00:17:51,917
IT WAS A GIANT,
FLYING BUFFALO, SIR,

338
00:17:51,959 --> 00:17:53,625
WITH AN EMPTY SADDLE.

339
00:17:53,667 --> 00:17:56,083
WHICH WAS IT,
A BUFFALO
OR A BISON?

340
00:17:56,125 --> 00:17:58,583
I-I-I'M NOT SURE
WHAT THE DIFFERENCE IS,

341
00:17:58,625 --> 00:18:00,959
BUT THAT'S NOT REALLY
THE POINT, IS IT, SIR?

342
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,959
I'LL DECIDE WHAT
THE POINT IS, FOOL!

343
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,125
AAH!

344
00:18:06,166 --> 00:18:08,083
[SPLASH]

345
00:18:08,125 --> 00:18:11,125
YOU! WAKE UP
THE CAPTAIN! SEARCH
THE ENTIRE RIG!

346
00:18:11,166 --> 00:18:12,208
SIR.

347
00:18:12,250 --> 00:18:14,000
WHAT?

348
00:18:14,041 --> 00:18:17,083
THAT WAS THE CAPTAIN
YOU JUST THREW OVERBOARD, SO--

349
00:18:17,125 --> 00:18:19,291
THEN WAKE UP
SOMEONE I HAVEN'T
THROWN OVERBOARD

350
00:18:19,333 --> 00:18:21,166
AND SEARCH THE RIG.

351
00:18:21,208 --> 00:18:24,125
THERE'S SOMETHING GOING ON HERE,
AND I DON'T LIKE IT.

352
00:18:28,125 --> 00:18:31,917
[PURRING]

353
00:18:31,959 --> 00:18:34,250
WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME.
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

354
00:18:34,291 --> 00:18:37,458
I WISH I KNEW HOW TO
MAKE A HURRICANE.

355
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:41,083
THE WARDEN WOULD RUN AWAY,
AND WE WOULD STEAL HIS KEYS.

356
00:18:41,125 --> 00:18:42,834
WOULDN'T HE JUST TAKE
HIS KEYS WITH HIM?

357
00:18:42,875 --> 00:18:44,417
I'M JUST TOSSING
IDEAS AROUND.

358
00:18:44,458 --> 00:18:46,000
I TRIED TALKING
THE EARTHBENDERS

359
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:48,417
INTO FIGHTING BACK,
BUT IT DIDN'T WORK.

360
00:18:48,458 --> 00:18:52,000
IF THERE WAS JUST
A WAY TO HELP THEM
HELP THEMSELVES.

361
00:18:52,041 --> 00:18:55,500
FOR THAT THEY NEED
SOME KIND OF EARTH
OR SOME ROCK,

362
00:18:55,542 --> 00:18:58,041
SOMETHING THEY CAN BEND.

363
00:18:58,083 --> 00:18:59,709
BUT THIS ENTIRE PLACE
IS MADE OF METAL.

364
00:19:02,291 --> 00:19:04,583
NO, IT'S NOT.
LOOK AT THE SMOKE.

365
00:19:04,625 --> 00:19:07,083
I BET THEY'RE BURNING COAL.

366
00:19:07,125 --> 00:19:08,834
IN OTHER WORDS...

367
00:19:08,875 --> 00:19:09,667
EARTH.

368
00:19:13,417 --> 00:19:16,000
IT'S ALMOST DAWN.
WE'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

369
00:19:16,041 --> 00:19:17,917
YOU SURE THIS IS
GONNA WORK?

370
00:19:17,959 --> 00:19:19,583
IT SHOULD.

371
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:20,875
THESE VENTS REMINDED ME
OF OUR LITTLE TRICK

372
00:19:20,917 --> 00:19:22,333
BACK AT THE VILLAGE.

373
00:19:22,375 --> 00:19:24,041
WE'RE GONNA DO
THE SAME THING,

374
00:19:24,083 --> 00:19:26,000
BUT ON A MUCH
BIGGER SCALE.

375
00:19:26,041 --> 00:19:27,834
THERE'S A HUGE DEPOSIT OF COAL
AT THE BASE OF THIS ISLAND.

376
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:29,959
AND THE WHOLE SYSTEM
IS VENTILATED.

377
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,000
AANG CLOSED OFF
ALL THE VENTS EXCEPT ONE.

378
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:33,750
WHEN HE DOES
HIS AIRBENDING,

379
00:19:33,792 --> 00:19:35,083
THE COAL ONLY HAS
ONE PLACE TO GO--

380
00:19:35,125 --> 00:19:36,458
RIGHT BACK HERE.

381
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:38,291
Man: THERE'S THE INTRUDER!

382
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:40,417
STAY BACK!
I'M WARNING YOU!

383
00:19:40,458 --> 00:19:43,041
KATARA, STOP.
YOU CAN'T WIN THIS FIGHT.

384
00:19:45,959 --> 00:19:48,583
LISTEN TO HIM WELL,
CHILD.

385
00:19:48,625 --> 00:19:50,750
YOU'RE
ONE MISTAKE AWAY

386
00:19:50,792 --> 00:19:52,875
FROM DYING
WHERE YOU STAND.

387
00:20:10,917 --> 00:20:13,583
[COUGHING]

388
00:20:13,625 --> 00:20:15,750
HERE'S YOUR CHANCE,
EARTHBENDERS!

389
00:20:15,792 --> 00:20:17,792
TAKE IT! YOUR FATE
IS IN YOUR OWN HANDS!

390
00:20:22,875 --> 00:20:24,458
[WARDEN LAUGHING]

391
00:20:26,875 --> 00:20:28,709
FOOLISH GIRL.

392
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:31,500
YOU THOUGHT A FEW
INSPIRATIONAL WORDS

393
00:20:31,542 --> 00:20:35,041
AND SOME COAL WOULD
CHANGE THESE PEOPLE?

394
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:39,375
LOOK AT THESE BLANK
HOPELESS FACES.

395
00:20:39,417 --> 00:20:42,375
THEIR SPIRITS
WERE BROKEN
A LONG TIME AGO.

396
00:20:42,417 --> 00:20:45,583
OH, BUT YOU STILL
BELIEVED IN THEM.

397
00:20:45,625 --> 00:20:48,166
HOW SWEET.

398
00:20:48,208 --> 00:20:51,750
THEY'RE A WASTE
OF YOUR ENERGY,
LITTLE GIRL.

399
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:54,333
YOU FAILED.

400
00:20:58,125 --> 00:20:58,917
GRR.

401
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:01,875
HYAH!

402
00:21:08,125 --> 00:21:09,959
SHOW NO MERCY!

403
00:21:12,750 --> 00:21:14,458
AAH!

404
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:15,625
FOR THE EARTH KINGDOM,

405
00:21:15,667 --> 00:21:17,291
ATTACK!

406
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:20,041
[ALL YELLING]

407
00:21:48,709 --> 00:21:49,375
[SCREAMING]

408
00:21:53,291 --> 00:21:55,291
GET TO THE SHIP!
WE'LL HOLD THEM OFF!

409
00:21:55,333 --> 00:21:57,417
DO NOT LET THEM ESCAPE!

410
00:22:01,208 --> 00:22:02,834
GUYS, THROW ME SOME COAL!

411
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:19,917
NO, PLEASE.
I CAN'T SWIM.

412
00:22:19,959 --> 00:22:22,625
DON'T WORRY.
I HEAR COWARDS FLOAT.

413
00:22:25,125 --> 00:22:27,291
[SCREAMING]

414
00:22:34,166 --> 00:22:37,041
I WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR SAVING ME, FOR SAVING US.

415
00:22:37,083 --> 00:22:39,083
ALL IT TOOK WAS
A LITTLE COAL.

416
00:22:39,125 --> 00:22:41,417
IT WASN'T THE COAL,
KATARA.

417
00:22:41,458 --> 00:22:43,125
IT WAS YOU.

418
00:22:43,166 --> 00:22:45,709
THANK YOU FOR HELPING ME
FIND MY COURAGE,

419
00:22:45,750 --> 00:22:47,333
KATARA OF
THE WATER TRIBE.

420
00:22:47,375 --> 00:22:50,333
MY FAMILY
AND EVERYONE HERE

421
00:22:50,375 --> 00:22:52,291
OWES YOU MUCH.

422
00:22:52,333 --> 00:22:54,667
SO, I GUESS
YOU'RE GOING HOME NOW.

423
00:22:54,709 --> 00:22:57,458
YES, TO TAKE BACK
MY VILLAGE.

424
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:59,959
TO TAKE BACK
ALL OF OUR VILLAGES!

425
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:02,166
THE FIRE NATION
WILL REGRET THE DAY

426
00:23:02,208 --> 00:23:04,083
THEY SET FOOT ON OUR LAND!

427
00:23:04,125 --> 00:23:05,166
[CHEERING]

428
00:23:05,208 --> 00:23:06,291
COME WITH US.

429
00:23:06,333 --> 00:23:07,792
I CAN'T.

430
00:23:07,834 --> 00:23:09,500
YOUR MISSION IS TO
TAKE BACK YOUR HOME.

431
00:23:09,542 --> 00:23:13,083
OURS IS TO GET AANG
TO THE NORTH POLE.

432
00:23:13,125 --> 00:23:15,750
THAT'S HIM,
ISN'T IT?
THE AVATAR.

433
00:23:18,041 --> 00:23:21,166
KATARA, THANK YOU
FOR BRINGING MY
FATHER BACK TO ME.

434
00:23:21,208 --> 00:23:23,333
I NEVER THOUGHT
I'D SEE HIM AGAIN.

435
00:23:23,375 --> 00:23:24,959
I ONLY WISH
THERE WAS SOME WAY--

436
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:27,041
I KNOW.

437
00:23:27,083 --> 00:23:29,458
MY MOTHER'S NECKLACE!
IT'S GONE!

438
00:23:50,959 --> 00:23:55,959
